{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_3","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' .claude/plans/active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Active Plan — Codex-Managed-Agent Roadmap Execution\n\nPlan anchor: `ROADMAP.md`\nWorkspace: `/home/clashuser/export/codex-managed-agent`\nMirror workspace: `/home/clashuser/hzh/work_bo/codex_manager/vscode-extension`\n\n## Mission\nExecute `ROADMAP.md` to completion through bounded codex-loop slices. Do not branch into unrelated ideas. After each slice, preserve stability, package the extension, sync the dev mirror, and record a new evolution note.\n\n## Milestone Status\n\n### Milestone 1 — Architecture Stabilization\nStatus: mostly complete\n\nCompleted:\n- thin `extension.js`\n- `src/panel.js` reduced toward orchestration\n- host modules split into `server`, `codex-link`, `commands`, `auto-continue`, `lifecycle`, `panel-view`, `state-sync`\n- webview template split into `board`, `insights`, `drawer`\n\nRemaining cleanup:\n- keep `panel.js` from regrowing\n- prefer new host/webview modules for future work\n\n### Milestone 2 — Board Interaction Quality\nStatus: complete\n\nTargets:\n- improve drag smoothness and drop reliability\n- finish resize behavior for all supported directions\n- define clear card-size semantics for `T / S / M / L`\n- keep `Needs Human` useful without blocking the board\n- ensure the board remains the single interactive layout surface\n\nCompleted in this milestone:\n- directional board resize now preserves anchored edges for north/west handles and persists the adjusted `col` / `row` / `cols` / `height`\n- board drop-preview clearing now resets correctly when the pointer leaves card and board boundaries\n- board density semantics now reserve preview text for `M / L`, keeping `S` as a title-plus-progress tier\n- `Needs Human` now auto-expands when urgent cards newly appear after an empty state, preventing hidden intervention work\n- collapsed `Needs Human` now keeps an urgent-count summary visible without reopening the compact dock\n- compact `Needs Human` cards no longer pulse like main-board intervention cards, reducing visual competition\n- board drag is now blocked when the gesture starts on card controls, reducing accidental layout edits\n- board drag-active feedback now appears immediately on dragstart instead of waiting for the first deferred indicator sync\n- board UI now spells out the `T / S / M / L` size ladder so density semantics are explicit instead of implicit\n\nExit review:\n- drag / resize and compact-surface behavior are now close to the Milestone 2 stability target\n- `Needs Human` no longer blocks the main board and remains visible in collapsed form\n- previous size-semantics gap is now addressed in board UI copy\n- exit confirmation complete: Milestone 2 now satisfies the roadmap exit criteria closely enough to move on\n\n### Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer\nStatus: active\n\nTargets:\n- stabilize usage report generation\n- improve topic map / word cloud / weekly shift interaction\n- make guidance more actionable and durable\n\nCurrent bounded slice:\n- audit current insight / report persistence paths and identify the first smallest reliability gap to fix next\n\n### Milestone 4 — Operational Reliability\nStatus: pending\n\nTargets:\n- background continue observability\n- clear loop status semantics\n- degraded-state handling\n- linked-vs-running distinction across surfaces\n\n### Milestone 5 — Publishable Product Quality\nStatus: pending\n\nTargets:\n- release workflow\n- screenshots / notes / docs\n- smoke validation routine\n- repo structure clarity\n\n## Slice Rules\n- Each tick completes one bounded, verifiable slice only.\n- Always validate syntax and package builds after code changes.\n- Always sync export repo changes back to the mirror workspace when behavior changes.\n- Always append an evolution note in `.claude/plans/loloop/`.\n- Update this active plan when milestone focus changes.\n\n## Immediate Next Slice Queue\n1. Milestone 3 persistence audit slice\n2. First bounded usage-report reliability fix\n3. Milestone 4 remains blocked behind Milestone 3\n4. Milestone 5 remains blocked behind Milestone 4\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
